    <p>Arunachal Pradesh, the largest state in north-east­ern In­dia, is nearly 84,000 sq km in land area. It has a pop­u­la­tion of more than 1.38 mil­lion.</p>
    <p>It shares in­ter­na­tional bor­ders with Bhutan to the west (160km), China to the north and north-east (1,080km) and Myan­mar to the east (440km). Its ter­rain ranges from snow-capped moun­tains in the north to river­ine plains in the south.</p>
    <p>China claims the state as part of “South Ti­bet”.</p>


